<h1>Configure Bria for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">CounterPath Bria (Solo, Teams, Enterprise) accepts standard SIP account credentials. Configuration is identical across desktop and mobile editions.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Steps (Bria 5 / Bria Solo desktop)</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <strong>Softphone → Account Settings → SIP Accounts</strong> (Windows) or <strong>Bria → Preferences → Accounts</strong> (macOS).</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Add</strong> and select <strong>SIP</strong>.</li>
		<li>Account tab:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Account name:</strong> VoiceTel</li>
				<li><strong>Protocol:</strong> SIP</li>
				<li><strong>User ID:</strong> SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Domain:</strong> SIP server host (shown in the customer portal)</li>
				<li><strong>Password:</strong> SIP password from onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Display name:</strong> the caller's name</li>
				<li><strong>Authorization name:</strong> same as User ID</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Topology tab:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Firewall traversal method:</strong> Use Local IP address (or Auto-detect)</li>
				<li>Leave STUN / TURN disabled unless engineering directed otherwise</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Transport tab:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Signaling transport:</strong> UDP</li>
				<li><strong>SIP listening port:</strong> Auto</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Voicemail tab: leave default unless onboarding gave a specific voicemail URI.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>OK</strong>; the account should show <strong>Registered</strong> within a few seconds.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Bria mobile (iOS / Android)</h2>
	<p>The mobile UI is similar but in a single Account screen:</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Open <strong>Settings → Accounts → Add</strong> → <strong>SIP</strong>.</li>
		<li>Enter the same fields: User ID, Domain, Password, Authorization name, Display name.</li>
		<li>Under <strong>Advanced</strong>: set Transport to UDP and Signal Encryption to None.</li>
		<li>Save. The account registers on cellular and Wi-Fi.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Codec preferences</h2>
	<p>Open <strong>Audio Codecs</strong> (desktop: <em>Preferences → Audio Codecs</em>; mobile: <em>Settings → Account → Codecs</em>). Enable PCMU, PCMA, and G.729; move PCMU to the top.</p>
</section>

